Media - Class in Files
Media extends MyFile and it is used for Media(mp3,mp4) file types

Constructor Media() Creates empty Media object changes media duration to 0 and media type to empty string
Media(int, String, String) - Constructor for class Files.Media
Constructor Media(int fileSize, String fileDir, String fileName) Creates New Media with given file size,directory, name assigns file name value to fileName variable(Same with fileDir,fileSize) assigns fileIcon new icon(media file icon) file name-should not include fullPath to the file) changes execution program and media type variables changes filesize variable
Media(String) - Constructor for class Files.Media

MyFile - Class in Files
Base file Class, it is used to store basic file data: file size, file name, file directory, creation time, modification time, execution program
MyFile() - Constructor for class Files.MyFile
Constructor MyFile() Creates empty MyFile object adds file icon
MyFile(int, String, String) - Constructor for class Files.MyFile
Constructor MyFile(int fileSize, String fileDir, String fileName) Creates New MyFile with given file size,directory, name assigns file name value to fileName variable(Same with fileDir,fileSize) assigns fileIcon new icon(txt file icon) file name-should not include fullPath to the file) creates Modification date and creation date
MyFile(String) - Constructor for class Files.MyFile
Constructor MyFile(String fileName) Creates New empty MyFile with given file name assigns file name value to fileName variable assigns fileIcon new icon(txt file icon) file name- should not include fullPath to the file)
